0. Important — Pre-Use Acknowledgments

   fudebako-agent operates as a deliberate exception to the host
   fudebako project's "data does not leave the client" policy. By using
   this software, you acknowledge and agree to the following:

   (a) Information you submit to the agent — including your prompts and
       any file contents the agent reads via its tools (such as files
       under /drive/) — is transmitted over HTTPS to the endpoint you
       configure (by default OpenRouter at https://openrouter.ai) and
       to the upstream model provider you select (Anthropic, OpenAI,
       Google, etc.).

   (b) The terms of service, privacy policies, data retention policies,
       billing, AND THE POSSIBILITY THAT TRANSMITTED DATA MAY BE USED BY
       THE RESPECTIVE SERVICE PROVIDER FOR MODEL TRAINING OR OTHER
       PURPOSES, apply directly between you and the respective service
       provider. The Author does not relay, resell, act as agent for, or
       warrant any such service.

   (c) API keys such as OPENROUTER_API_KEY are stored by you in
       browser-local storage (/drive/) and are not included in the
       distribution. Acquisition, safekeeping, revocation, and response
       to misuse of the keys are your responsibility.

   (d) When you carry out conversations with the agent, the conversation
       history — including prompts, AI responses, and tool inputs and
       outputs — is persisted to your browser-local storage at
       /drive/.fudebako-agent/history/. You acknowledge the risk of
       third-party exposure of this history in shared-browser
       environments or in the event of device loss. You can delete the
       history at any time via the session-list UI.

   (e) You are responsible for complying with the terms of service of
       the third-party services described in Section 3.2 (OpenRouter
       and the upstream model provider you select). This includes the
       age requirements set by those services and the export-control
       laws applicable to your location and to the destination of your
       requests (including, without limitation, U.S. EAR and Japan's
       Foreign Exchange and Foreign Trade Act).

