3. Third-Party Components and Third-Party Services

   3.1 Third-Party Components.

       fudebako-agent is distributed as part of the host fudebako
       standalone HTML artifact. The distributed HTML includes
       third-party software components bundled by fudebako (Pyodide,
       Tailwind CSS, the Noto fonts, and others), each of which is
       licensed to you separately under its own terms. See
       docs/THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md and the NOTICES.txt accompanying
       each release for the complete list and applicable license texts.
       Nothing in these terms supersedes those third-party licenses.

   3.2 Third-Party Services.

       fudebako-agent issues HTTPS requests to external services
       operated by third parties (OpenRouter and the upstream model
       provider you select) on the basis of your interaction with the
       agent. The code of those services is not bundled with
       fudebako-agent; their availability, response quality, pricing,
       and data handling are governed entirely by the respective
       service providers. The Author has no contractual relationship
       with these services and is not responsible for the acts or
       omissions of any service provider.

       For users located in the European Economic Area (EEA), data
       transmissions to these third-party services may be subject to
       the GDPR and other applicable data-protection laws. Exercise of
       data-subject rights (access, rectification, erasure, restriction
       of processing, etc.) should be directed to the respective
       service providers. Because the Author does not process user data
       (see Section 6), the Author does not act as a data controller or
       processor for these transmissions.

4. No Warranty

   FUDEBAKO-AGENT IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE", WITHOUT
   WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, WHETHER EXPRESS, IMPLIED, OR STATUTORY. TO
   THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, THE AUTHOR
   EXPRESSLY DISCLAIMS ALL IMPLIED WARRANTIES, INCLUDING WARRANTIES
   OF MERCHANTABILITY, NON-INFRINGEMENT, AND FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR
   PURPOSE. THE AUTHOR DOES NOT WARRANT THAT FUDEBAKO-AGENT WILL MEET
   YOUR REQUIREMENTS, OPERATE WITHOUT INTERRUPTION, OR BE ERROR-FREE.

   In addition, you expressly acknowledge:

   (a) AI Output Accuracy. Responses produced by fudebako-agent are
       generated by a large language model. They may contain factual
       errors, hallucinations (plausible-sounding but incorrect
       content), or inappropriate or harmful output. The Author makes
       no warranty as to the accuracy, currency, lawfulness, or
       fitness for any particular purpose of such output. Reliance on
       AI output for material decisions is your responsibility.

   (b) Tool-Execution Side Effects and Prompt Injection. Based on
       the model's judgment, fudebako-agent invokes tools including
       Python code execution (run_python) and read/write operations
       against browser-local storage (read_drive, write_drive,
       list_drive). While these executions take place within the
       Pyodide sandbox and the browser's storage boundary, you should
       be specifically aware of:

       - Network communication. Python code executed inside Pyodide
         can issue arbitrary HTTP/HTTPS requests via the browser's
         fetch API or equivalent. The term "sandbox" here refers to
         isolation of the code-execution environment; it does NOT
         block outbound network communication.

       - Storage side effects. Modification or deletion of data under
         your /drive/ may occur.

       - Prompt injection. If file contents read by the agent (via
         read_drive or similar) or external resources fetched by the
         agent contain text that the model interprets as instructions,
         tool calls you did not intend — including arbitrary Python
         execution and exfiltration of /drive/ contents — may be
         induced.

       You are responsible for verifying the results and side effects
       of tool execution. The Author recommends exercising particular
       caution when allowing the agent to read files or external
       resources from untrusted sources, and not placing
       sensitive-handling material (private keys, credentials,
       personally identifiable information) under /drive/.

   (c) Scheduled Execution. The scheduling feature re-runs the agent
       in the same browser UI at times you specify. Execution is
       limited to periods when the browser tab is open, but
       unintended tool calls and external-API charges may occur at
       times you did not actively initiate.

